Police have arrested a man who allegedly attacked his estranged wife with machetes in Megenche village leaving her for dead.
Ms Naomy Nyangarisa, 22, is nursing injuries to her head, hands, legs and face after escaping death by a whisker during the gruesome attack on Friday.
When the Nation visited her at Tabaka Mission Hospital where she had been admitted, she was preparing to move to another hospital for specialised treatment.



