“We had stayed together for four years, but we parted ways in June last year, and I decided to get married elsewhere,” Ms Nyangarisa said.
She added that the suspect stormed her new home wielding two pangas and attacked her.
 “He first tried to attack my husband and, when I intervened, he hacked me on the hand and both legs,” she said.
Lying helpless
Angry locals turned on the suspect, slashing him on both hands, but he managed to escape. He was later arrested and is held at Tabaka Police Station.



