County Police Commander Jebel Monene said officers were informed by locals of a woman, who had been attacked and was lying helpless in her house.
“When we rushed to the scene on Friday, we found a woman with serious cuts on the floor. She was in pain and seemed to be regaining her consciousness,” Mr Monene told the Nation on phone.
With the help of the residents, the police rushed her to Nyangena Hospital but her family failed to raise the Sh10,000 admission fee.
